WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-ES

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:01.334
In Return of the Ancients,

00:00:01.334 --> 00:00:05.672
we're adding a set of challenges
for the first time in a PoE 2 league.

00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.574
Every two challenges you complete will

00:00:07.574 --> 00:00:10.193
earn you a piece of the
Knight of Aldur armor set,

00:00:10.193 --> 00:00:11.795
so they're definitely worth trying to complete.

00:00:12.362 --> 00:00:15.148
To check your progress and see
what you need to complete a challenge,

00:00:15.148 --> 00:00:17.801
press 'H' to open the challenges screen.

00:00:17.951 --> 00:00:19.319
There are eight challenges in total,

00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:22.222
and they range from fairly easy
to quite difficult.

00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.923
To complete "The Rune Finder" you

00:00:23.923 --> 00:00:26.626
will need to find remnants
with large amounts of slots

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:28.595
and use them to craft new items.

00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:32.999
Seven-slot builds can
be very challenging with six waves of enemies,

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:36.002
so attempting these fights
requires some skill.

00:00:38.638 --> 00:00:39.639
During the campaign,

00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:41.408
there are many optional bosses.

00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:42.959
To complete "The Hunter",

00:00:42.959 --> 00:00:45.361
you will have to hunt six more.

00:00:45.361 --> 00:00:49.282
The last two, Akthi, the Last Stinger
and Anundr, the Sandworm,

00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:51.551
can be difficult to find,
as they are in The Crossroads of Khari.

00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:55.271
To find them, follow the dry riverbed.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:57.073
You'll find its sand at the end.

00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:00.877
The Ascendant requires you to earn all eight points

00:01:00.877 --> 00:01:03.880
of your ancestry class
by completing ancestry tests.

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:06.766
Getting the final set of points
can be very challenging.

00:01:06.766 --> 00:01:10.220
You can kill Zarokh on the fourth
level of the Trial of the Sekhemas

00:01:10.653 --> 00:01:14.390
or defeat the Master of Trials
by finding the three keys.

00:01:15.141 --> 00:01:16.960
Of the two, the Test of Chaos will

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:20.029
take you much longer to
complete the test many times,

00:01:20.029 --> 00:01:22.549
but the Test of the Sekhemas
is more challenging,

00:01:22.549 --> 00:01:25.151
so you will have to decide which
of the two paths you will take.

00:01:26.719 --> 00:01:28.138
"The reliquary" is simple.

00:01:28.138 --> 00:01:30.573
Identify 50 different unique objects.   Are

00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.910
you having trouble finding unique items?

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.647
Jado, the Atlas Master, has
many skills focused on finding them.

00:01:39.749 --> 00:01:41.151
To complete "The Craftsman"

00:01:41.151 --> 00:01:43.720
you will need to use several
different crafting objects.  They

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.839
all come from remnant encounters.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:48.441
For "The Cartographer"

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.894
you will have to assign the entire Atlas tree.

00:01:51.177 --> 00:01:52.712
The 300 nodes.

00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:56.883
You can do it slowly by completing
all the maps inside the fortress,

00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:58.918
but there is another way.

00:01:58.918 --> 00:02:01.054
Each time you defeat the Arbiter of Divinity,

00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:05.175
you will automatically complete
a large section of the fortress.

00:02:06.676 --> 00:02:09.679
Find keys to this fight
by exploring the Citadels in the Atlas.  They

00:02:09.829 --> 00:02:12.832
all have large, bright beams,
so you'll be able to see them in the fog.

00:02:13.032 --> 00:02:16.719
After facing him four times,
you will be able to complete the entire fortress.

00:02:17.871 --> 00:02:21.040
And last but not least
, "The Victor".

00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:24.010
This challenge requires you to kill
three final bosses,

00:02:24.010 --> 00:02:25.478
the toughest fights in the game.

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.030
Tangmazu,

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:28.097
the Bodach

00:02:28.097 --> 00:02:29.682
and the Kulemak Vessel.

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:34.070
These are the final bosses of the
Delirium, Ritual, and Abyss leagues,

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.190
so you'll need to complete
three quest lines for this challenge.

00:02:37.674 --> 00:02:39.909
However, there is something important about
Kulemak's Vessel,

00:02:39.909 --> 00:02:42.162
and that is that you must defeat it
while it has its full strength.

00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.113
This means risking the item
during the boss fight by

00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.716
pulling back the finger and defeating it afterwards.

00:02:49.352 --> 00:02:50.303
As I said before, for

00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:53.223
every two challenges you complete,
you'll get pieces of the armor set,

00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:55.675
so you don't have to complete them
to get some rewards.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:58.628
But if you do, you'll be able to show off your feat,

00:02:58.778 --> 00:03:02.715
because everyone in the global chat and
forums will be able to see how many challenges you've completed.

00:03:03.149 --> 00:03:05.835
You'll also get this
totem decoration for your lair,

00:03:05.835 --> 00:03:07.837
meaning
those who trade with you

00:03:07.837 --> 00:03:10.840
will be able to see that you were there
and defeated the league.

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:15.361
Try to complete these challenges and more on
May 29 in Return of the Ancients.

00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:17.463
Thanks for watching the video, see you there.

